1. Molim vas da nam *otkrijete* svoje namere. (Please reveal to us your intentions.)
2. Da li biste želeli da *otkrijemo* novi restoran zajedno? (Would you like us to discover a new restaurant together?)
3. Kada *otkrijemo* istinu, bićemo slobodni. (When we discover the truth, we will be free.)
4. Ako se *otkriješ* pred nama, možemo ti pomoći. (If you reveal yourself to us, we can help you.)
5. Želela bih da *otkrijem* nešto što me tišti. (I would like to disclose something that is troubling me.)
6. Nismo sigurni da li će se tajna *otkriti*. (We are not sure if the secret will be revealed.)
7. Moramo *otkriti* ko je ukrao novac. (We have to uncover who stole the money.)
8. Želim da *otkrijem* svoju stranu priče. (I want to reveal my side of the story.)
9. Ne želimo da *otkrijemo* svoje planove pre vremena. (We do not want to disclose our plans ahead of time.)
10. Nadamo se da će se istina *otkriti* uskoro. (We hope that the truth will be uncovered soon.)

(Note: In Serbian, the word "otkrijemo" is a verb in the present tense and it means "we reveal/uncover/discover". In the examples above, it appears in different forms, such as "otkrijete", "otkriješ", "otkriti", etc., depending on the subject and the tense.)